        "title": "refactor: share QA runtime helpers",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Move shared QA markdown report rendering, live-lane artifact/error helpers, output tee, and Docker runtime helpers into the existing private local-only `openclaw/plugin-sdk/qa-runtime` seam.\n- Keep the public `openclaw/plugin-sdk/qa-runner-runtime` subpath focused on the existing QA runner discovery/loading contract, with no public SDK API baseline update.\n- Replace duplicated QA Lab and QA Matrix implementations with shared helper imports and thin Docker runtime adapters.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/check-plugin-sdk-subpath-exports.mjs`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugin-sdk/qa-runtime.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/qa-runner-runtime.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-lab/src`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-matrix/src`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 <touched files>`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\nBehavior addressed: QA Lab and QA Matrix now share report, live-lane artifact/error, output tee, and Docker runtime helper code instead of carrying duplicated implementations.\nReal environment tested: local Codex worktree on macOS with repo dependencies installed.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: the verification commands listed above were run after the final patch state.\nEvidence after fix: focused private helper tests, QA Lab source tests, QA Matrix source tests, build, SDK subpath export check, scoped formatting, diff whitespace check, and autoreview all passed.\nObserved result after fix: existing QA Lab and Matrix tests continue passing while duplicate helper modules are removed or reduced to adapters, helper-only code stays on the private `qa-runtime` seam, and the public SDK API baseline hash is reverted to the tracked main value.\nWhat was not tested: no live Docker QA lane or live transport credential-backed run was executed. `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check` was not listed as passing because the tracked baseline hash currently fails the same check on a clean `origin/main` worktree; this PR no longer carries that unrelated hash update.\n",
